f manly virtue\\\" without women athletes, the modern Olympics will reach gender parity for the first time during the 2024 Paris Games, 128 years since its first edition.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTO\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 344}, {\"ngram\": \"REUTERS PublishedJun\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"PM\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"PARIS\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 421}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"celebration\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 449}, {\"ngram\": \"manly virtue\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 465}, {\"ngram\": \"women athletes\", \"from\": 475, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"gender parity\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 535}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 554}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Games\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 582}, {\"ngram\": \"128 years\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"its first edition\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the ancient Greek event was revived by French aristocrat Pierre de Coubertin in the late 19th century, he saw it as a celebration of gentlemanly athleticism \\\"with female applause as its reward\\\".\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.7630048487750031, \"rank\": 0.30722036633224775, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7981136314154976, \"rank\": 0.25024897043236893, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 685, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res